.
</emphasis>
Aedeagal tube sclerotized, slightly S-shaped in lateral aspect. Sac short, ca 1/3 as long as the tube (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D696E7764209F2FB7CE4421DD4745E96" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Neoperla hajeki sp. nov. (male) A aedeagus with everted sac, dorsal view B aedeagus with everted sac, ventral view C aedeagus with everted sac, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667991" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal sac bearing a subapical triangular patch of spinules in dorsal aspect (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="29B1A4D931679100AB1F04CA2C37129C" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Neoperla hajeki sp. nov. (male) A aedeagus with everted sac, dorsal view B aedeagus with everted sac, ventral view C aedeagus with everted sac, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667991" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4A</figureCitation>
), remainder bald except a few ventral spinules (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BD1495F61265B33750BCE29C9668992F" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Neoperla hajeki sp. nov. (male) A aedeagus with everted sac, dorsal view B aedeagus with everted sac, ventral view C aedeagus with everted sac, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667991" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4B, C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8984D27204F5CE7CD350CFEDCE8DF7E7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="866093EC642286D0025645DD633EC6C3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Female</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3911BAF26BEE4BD493FD63654355478A" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Neoperla hajeki sp. nov. (male) A head and pronotum, dorsal view B terminalia, dorsal view C vagina, dorsal view D vagina, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-B); 0.2 mm (C-D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667992" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 9.3-9.6 mm, hind wing length 8.2-8.4 mm. General color pattern is similar to males. The subgential plate of sternum 8 is not produced posteriorly. Vagina large and apically slender, spiral and incurved, apical round, full of scaly spots. Spermatheca small, its origin in the terminal vagina.
</paragraph>
<caption id="650887757CE6B16C0EABCB0FA8C8AD46" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667992" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
