<paragraph id="21635F6DC601AA3CE9F10A92ABC83672" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="4C76D19576EBD3C910C6CF4CD4CC9A4B" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Egg</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6378B4ECD87ABC3D02C50D2479894727" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Neoperla hajeki sp. nov. (egg) A egg B lid C collar D collar and lid E FCIs and lid F micropyles." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667993" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6</figureCitation>
). Chorion length 346-348 
<normalizedToken id="4F20C5E7F590367D05ECE4CFF914723C" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, width 173-177 
<normalizedToken id="BFAB689C3513AD09795A2F2EEE94166A" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Micropyles 3 with rims, placed ca 1/3 length near opercullum, each located between striae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="335C8FA4E6ABBADB0652FE5D7807D9FB" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Neoperla hajeki sp. nov. (egg) A egg B lid C collar D collar and lid E FCIs and lid F micropyles." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667993" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6A, F</figureCitation>
). Collar not distinctly stalked, but slightly constricted at base; width ca 79.5 
<normalizedToken id="8073ED2D6823DFFC4BCD2DC7BA221E51" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
at collar (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="35F5968AA84015A0AFF387BE5A873AC4" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Neoperla hajeki sp. nov. (egg) A egg B lid C collar D collar and lid E FCIs and lid F micropyles." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667993" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6D</figureCitation>
). Collar short, irregular in shape (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5CFE0E6AC43EDB3E76C2FBBC88059F70" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Neoperla hajeki sp. nov. (egg) A egg B lid C collar D collar and lid E FCIs and lid F micropyles." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667993" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6D</figureCitation>
). Rim slightly flanged, margin irregularly scalloped. Chorion with striate on lid and collar. FCIs on lid distinct; cells with thin, smooth walls and floors punctuated (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4D40E8305E6C86CD611BEFF6A6ACFDCA" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Neoperla hajeki sp. nov. (egg) A egg B lid C collar D collar and lid E FCIs and lid F micropyles." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.78069.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667993" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6B, E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
